54#ifdef _MSC_VER
55/*
56 * Under MSVC, functions exported by a loadable module must be marked
57 * "dllexport". Other compilers don't need that.
58 * Borrowed from PostgreSQL file win32.h
59 */
60#define PGDLLEXPORT __declspec (dllexport)
61/*
62 * Avoids warning C4996: 'strdup': The POSIX name for this item is deprecated.
63 */
64#define strdup _strdup
65#endif

74#define DOUBLE_PAD(size) ( (size) + ((size) % 8 ? (8 - (size) % 8) : 0 ) )
75
79typedef struct
80{
81 int32 vl_len_;
82 uint8 settype;
83 uint8 basetype;
84 int16 flags;
85 int32 count;
86 int32 maxcount;
87 int16 bboxsize;
88} Set;
89
93typedef struct
94{
95 uint8 spantype;
96 uint8 basetype;
97 bool lower_inc;
98 bool upper_inc;
99 char padding[4];
100 Datum lower;
101 Datum upper;
102} Span;
103
107typedef struct
108{
109 int32 vl_len_;
110 uint8 spansettype;
111 uint8 spantype;
112 uint8 basetype;
113 char padding;
114 int32 count;
115 int32 maxcount;
116 Span span;
117 Span elems[1];
118} SpanSet;
119
123typedef struct
124{
125 Span period;
126 Span span;
127 int16 flags;
128} TBox;
129
133typedef struct
134{
135 Span period;
136 double xmin;
137 double ymin;
138 double zmin;
139 double xmax;
140 double ymax;
141 double zmax;
142 int32_t srid;
143 int16 flags;
144} STBox;

201typedef struct
202{
203 int32 vl_len_;
204 uint8 temptype;
205 uint8 subtype;
206 int16 flags;
207 int32 count;
208 int32 maxcount;
209 int16 bboxsize;
210 char padding[6];
211 Span period;
215 /* variable-length data follows */
216} TSequence;

224{
225 int32 vl_len_;
226 uint8 temptype;
227 uint8 subtype;
228 int16 flags;
229 int32 count;

233 int16 bboxsize;
234 int16 padding;
235 Span period;
239 /* variable-length data follows */
240} TSequenceSet;

280/*****************************************************************************
281 * Error codes
282 *****************************************************************************/
283
284typedef enum
285{
286 MEOS_SUCCESS = 0, // Successful operation
287
288 MEOS_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR = 1, // Unspecified internal error
289 MEOS_ERR_INTERNAL_TYPE_ERROR = 2, // Internal type error
290 MEOS_ERR_VALUE_OUT_OF_RANGE = 3, // Internal out of range error
291 MEOS_ERR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO = 4, // Internal division by zero error
292 MEOS_ERR_MEMORY_ALLOC_ERROR = 5, // Internal malloc error
293 MEOS_ERR_AGGREGATION_ERROR = 6, // Internal aggregation error
294 MEOS_ERR_DIRECTORY_ERROR = 7, // Internal directory error
295 MEOS_ERR_FILE_ERROR = 8, // Internal file error
296
297 MEOS_ERR_INVALID_ARG = 10, // Invalid argument
298 MEOS_ERR_INVALID_ARG_TYPE = 11, // Invalid argument type
299 MEOS_ERR_INVALID_ARG_VALUE = 12, // Invalid argument value
300 MEOS_ERR_FEATURE_NOT_SUPPORTED = 13, // Feature not currently supported
301
302 MEOS_ERR_MFJSON_INPUT = 20, // MFJSON input error
303 MEOS_ERR_MFJSON_OUTPUT = 21, // MFJSON output error
304 MEOS_ERR_TEXT_INPUT = 22, // Text input error
305 MEOS_ERR_TEXT_OUTPUT = 23, // Text output error
306 MEOS_ERR_WKB_INPUT = 24, // WKB input error
307 MEOS_ERR_WKB_OUTPUT = 25, // WKB output error
308 MEOS_ERR_GEOJSON_INPUT = 26, // GEOJSON input error
309 MEOS_ERR_GEOJSON_OUTPUT = 27, // GEOJSON output error
310
311} errorCode;
